Textron Inc's Avco Lycoming Textronsubsidiary said it finalized a 1.4 billion dlr five-yearcontract with the U.S. Army for M1 Abrams main battle tank gasturbine engines.    Under the contract, Avco said the army will procure 3,299installed engines plus spare engines and a combination ofmodules and gear boxes.    It also said the agreement includes an initial purchase of173 engines by the U.S. Marines under a program that willresult in a fleet of 560 M1 tanks. Reuter&#3;